The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of 12:26 p.m. local time.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  decreased 0.2 percent to 14,492.83, while
the  Colcap Index (COLCAP)  fell 0.4 percent to 1,720.60.  Oil producers gained as crude in  New York  rose from the
lowest close in seven months.  Pacific Rubiales Energy Corp. (PRE)  , which operates
 Colombia â€™s largest oil field, advanced 1.2 percent to 47,180
pesos.  Petrominerales Ltd. (PMG)  , a Calgary-based  oil
